<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="49" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="49">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="49">
The 
<normalizedToken originalValue="authors’">authors'</normalizedToken>
collection from 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Incertae sedis Basidiomycota" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Mycelium" order="Incertae sedis Basidiomycota" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Pandanaceae</taxonomicName>
host in Thailand was identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pestalotiopsidaceae" genus="Pestalotiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pestalotiopsis jiangxiensis" order="Amphisphaeriales" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jiangxiensis">Pestalotiopsis jiangxiensis</taxonomicName>
. This taxon grouped with 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Pestalotiopsidaceae" genus="Pestalotiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Pestalotiopsis jiangxiensis" order="Amphisphaeriales" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jiangxiensis">Pestalotiopsis jiangxiensis</taxonomicName>
LC4399 which is collected from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Pentaphylacaceae" genus="Eurya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eurya" order="Ericales" pageId="24" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Eurya</taxonomicName>
sp., with high bootstrap support of 100% in ML.
</paragraph>
